The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a hidden hypergraph using additive queries, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses information theoretic bounds to prove the optimality of their query complexity, which falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorial algorithms and complexity theory, which are subfields of computer science that fall under cs.CC and cs.DM. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of finding hidden structures, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, falling under cs.SI.
